The article announces the authorization of a safe and effective COVID-19 vaccine for children aged 5 to 11. It highlights that this development will alleviate parents' worries and reduce the spread of the virus among children. The administration has secured enough vaccine supply for all children in America and has started shipping out doses to various locations. The vaccination program will be fully operational by the week of November 8, with vaccination sites including pharmacies, pediatrician's offices, and schools. The article emphasizes that the vaccine for children will build upon the progress made in vaccinating adults, with over 78% of Americans aged 12 and older having received at least one shot.